author: cbs8
title: Warrant seeks return of assault suspect from Fla. To Miss.
text:
OCEAN SPRINGS, Miss. (AP) - Mississippi Gov. Phil Bryant has signed a warrant seeking to have a suspect in a sexual assault extradited from Florida to face charges in Ocean Springs.
Bryant spokeswoman Nicole Webb confirms to The Associated Press on Wednesday that the governor has signed the warrant to have 24-year-old Cameron May, of Biloxi, returned to Mississippi.
Jackson County District Attorney Tony Lawrence told the Mississippi Press ( http://bit.ly/1VRWCqc ) that transferring May could take two weeks. May was captured Sept. 21 in Florida and refused to waive his right to an extradition hearing. The governor's warrant eliminates the need for the hearing.
It was not immediately clear whether May has an attorney. He is accused of attacking a 33-year-old woman Sept. 10 in Ocean Springs.
The AP does not identify victims of sexual assault.
